Starcomms of Nigeria Snaps Two-Day Gain After Reporting Loss

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-05-13T11:22:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/starcomms-of-nigeria-snaps-two-day-gain-after-reporting-loss.html
     May 13 (Bloomberg)--  Starcomms Plc (STARCOMM) , a Nigerian company that
offers fixed-line and mobile telephone services, snapped two
days of gains after reporting a full-year loss.  The stock lost 2 kobo, or 2.6 percent, to 76 kobo by 11:47
a.m. in Lagos, taking its decline this year to 47 percent,
compared with a gain of 5.4 percent in the  Nigerian Stock
Exchange  All-Share Index.  The company reported a loss of 7.7 billion naira ($49
million) for the period through December, compared with a loss
of 7.8 billion naira a year earlier, the Lagos-based company
said in a statement on the website of the Nigerian Stock
Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 